3:
Ladies and gentlemen... Now, for the
moment you've all been waiting for!
7:
No matter what world you're on,
blood sports sell.
8:
But this ain't a bandwagon I ever
saw Stella jumping on.
13:
No, no. She's not here for fun. She
got some mysterious invitation.
21:
Stepping into a ring teeming with
deadly monsters...
22:
Is a heart-throb weaponsmaster
from the Farlands!
34:
Hah... Monsters, you rush at your
doom.
38:
Blade of the fiends, Inferno...
Blade of the ghouls, Kamaitachi...
Blade of the droids, Genos...
Lend me your power!
40: This night, red flowers shall bloom.
43:
I can't believe my eyes! Ladies and
gentlemen, he's trounced the
monsters without moving an inch!
46:
Were you watching? That was the
strength of Libram Swes.
47:
I've rented a room where we can
speak. Please, follow me.
59:
You are nobility, then, from the
neighboring kingdom.
63:
Yes. Do you not know of the
Farlands' Nine Noble Houses? Each
forms a pillar that upholds our
homeland.
66:
My house, Swes, commands all
commerce. We are a collection of
traders and diplomats, for our most
important business is conducted
with foreign clients.
74:
Amazing? We are the veins through
which the lifeblood of our country
flows!
79:
Is that why you take part in
Palpebra's blood sport? To curry
favor?
83:
Yes. Adventurers value two
things—strength and beauty. I have
proven myself to have both in
abundance.
85:
No doubt this city shall be more
willing to open its gates if I am the
one knocking.
91:
Hah. But attract enough eyes, and
soon they'll see you're a fraud.
97:
In the arena, it is true you seized
victory against overwhelming odds.
But did you seize it by your own
hand? It seemed your weapons
were fighting for you.
102:
Do you mean to say I have no
strength of my own?
106:
Because you would be right. Without
my blades, I am no warrior!
112:
Why... Why does it sound like you're
bragging?
117:
But... I did select my arsenal by my
own hand. My blades were all
unearthed in the darkest corners of
the Kaleidoscope, in power rivaling
even the mythical weapons of the
Farlands!
120:
What's more, I paid for them out of
my own purse. That is where my true
strength lies! Not on the battlefield,
but in the market! And in many
cases, the coin is more powerful
than the sword.
126:
But now, let us speak of why I have
summoned you here.
127:
I desire to buy information from you.
Or shall I say... "about" you?
130:
Palpebra is a city of strange folk and
stranger happenings. But even in
this menagerie of oddities, you are
singularly curious.
132:
I can see that those two are not
gargans... I believe they came from
a place beyond the Kaleido—
137:
We're not selling you anything. We're
going home.
141:
Wait. Won't you at least listen to the
terms?
151: But I haven't even named a—
154:
Hah. I see your game now. It's one
you needn't play with me. I will pay
anything you deem fair.
159:
I don't want your money. I would like
you to move.
165:
Go spend your dough somewhere
else.
171:
If I can't buy your trust, at least give
me a chance to earn it! I have
nothing to hide!
173:
I am a man so immersed in
pursuing material goods, I've never
had any friends!
174:
W-well? I've been honest with you.
Now it is your turn to be honest with
me!
183: So you wish to learn more about us?
186:
Yes! That's what I've been saying
from the start!
197:
*sigh* For once, I thought she was
just gonna kick 'em to the curb.
207:
Ha... Hahaha... I can't believe my
eyes.
210:
A portal between worlds. If my father
and brother knew of my discovery,
how proud they—
215:
Hey. You better not be getting any
funny ideas.
223:
I'm not! I would never sell
information on Starview!
225:
This is the most valuable port to
ever exist—the sole trade route
extending into other worlds! And it is
all mine!
227:
Rejoice! You lot are my newest
investment! Hahaha!
